Molly Parks, 24, was found in the bathroom of the pizza restaurant where she worked in Manchester, New Hampshire, on April 16 .
Her father, Tom Parks, said he knew that when police turned up on his doorstep, they were there about Molly .
Days later, he wrote an obituary about her struggle with addiction to heroin and prescription pills .
'She fought her addiction for at least five years and had experienced a near fatal overdose before it is too late,' he wrote .